se a product or service aidan turner irish actor best known for his roles as kíli in the threepart fantasy film the hobbit and john mitchell in the supernatural drama series being human after graduating from the gaiety school of acting in  aidan turner appeared in several theatre plays including the plough and the stars romeo and juliet and a cry from heaven his television acting career began in  with a guest appearance on the tudors and then in the sixpart television drama serial about the preraphaelite brotherhood desperate romantics playing dante gabriel rossetti between  and  he appeared in a recurring role as ruairí mcgowan in the clinic followed by playing the vampire john mitchell in the supernatural drama programme being human being human was crowned best drama series at the  tv choice awards and best television drama series at writers’ guild continue reading » alan davies standup comedian writer and actor best known for playing the title role in jonathan creek and as a permanent panellist on qi alan davies began performing standup comedy in  at the whitstable labour club and was named time out’s best young comic in  he continued touring and performing in the uk and australia winning the edinburgh festival critics award for comedy in  in  and  he hosted alan’s big one for three series on radio  before appearing in channel ’s spoof travel show one for the road alan played the title role in jonathan creek between  and  the character worked as a creative consultant to a stage magician while also solving seemingly supernatural mysteries through his talent for logical deduction and understanding of illusions the show won a bafta for best drama and continue reading » alexander armstrong alexander is a brilliant british comedian actor and television presenter known for being one half of double act armstrong and miller with ben miller and as a frequent presenter of the satirical panel show have i got news for you he graduated in  soon after he moved to london with s